703319f-a.text:
Brighton Beach Ave., (left) south side, between Ocean Parkway and Coney Island Ave., (general view) showing some two hundred bungalows,beyond which may be seen the Brighton Beach Hotel, at the foot of Coney Island Ave. The Brighton Beach Line partially seen, runs on Brighton Beach Ave., at this point.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
703319f-a.folder: Brighton Beach Avenue & Ocean Parkway, Brooklyn, NY
703319f-a.original_title: Brooklyn: Brighton Beach Avenue - Ocean Parkway

706120f-a.text:
Oeean Parkway, east side, south of 4he Brighton Beach Ave., (view taken from elevated station of the Brighton Subway Line of the B.M.T.), showing from left to right the Parkway Baths (in back of the New Brighton Theatre), the theatre, and the People's Bathing Pavilion. In the background, at the
right, is the Atlantic Ocean.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
